Before writing any code, read:
- docs/AIS_Architecture_Guidelines.md
- docs/AIS_Architecture_Context.md

# Non-negotiables:
- Every Supabase query: .eq('org_id', user.orgId)
- Every team query: .in('team_id', user.teamIds)
- Identity only from src/lib/auth.js — never hardcode IDs
- Colours via CSS variables only — no hardcoded hex
- scoring.js is frozen — never modify it
- Every new table needs org_id non-nullable
- Every await inside try/catch
- No component over 400 lines without a split plan
- Name the exact file to modify in every prompt

# Current V-stage: V1.5
Do not implement V2 or V3 features.

# When uncertain:
Ask: does this work for one org AND ten orgs each with twenty teams?